{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
    "chapterNumber": 11,
    "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11",
    "summary": "Source text for 1 Corinthians 11 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:1",
      "text": "Be ye followers of me, even as I also am of Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:2",
      "text": "Now I praise you, brethren, that ye remember me in all things, and keep the ordinances, as I delivered them to you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:3",
      "text": "But I would have you know, that the head of every man is Christ; and the head of the woman is the man; and the head of Christ is God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:4",
      "text": "Every man praying or prophesying, having his head covered, dishonoureth his head.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:5",
      "text": "But every woman that prayeth or prophesieth with her head uncovered dishonoureth her head: for that is even all one as if she were shaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:6",
      "text": "For if the woman be not covered, let her also be shorn: but if it be a shame for a woman to be shorn or shaven, let her be covered.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:7",
      "text": "For a man indeed ought not to cover his head, forasmuch as he is the image and glory of God: but the woman is the glory of the man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:8",
      "text": "For the man is not of the woman; but the woman of the man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:9",
      "text": "Neither was the man created for the woman; but the woman for the man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:10",
      "text": "For this cause ought the woman to have power on her head because of the angels.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:11",
      "text": "Nevertheless neither is the man without the woman, neither the woman without the man, in the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:12",
      "text": "For as the woman is of the man, even so is the man also by the woman; but all things of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:13",
      "text": "Judge in yourselves: is it comely that a woman pray unto God uncovered?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:14",
      "text": "Doth not even nature itself teach you, that, if a man have long hair, it is a shame unto him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:15",
      "text": "But if a woman have long hair, it is a glory to her: for her hair is given her for a covering.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:16",
      "text": "But if any man seem to be contentious, we have no such custom, neither the churches of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:17",
      "text": "Now in this that I declare unto you I praise you not, that ye come together not for the better, but for the worse.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:18",
      "text": "For first of all, when ye come together in the church, I hear that there be divisions among you; and I partly believe it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:19",
      "text": "For there must be also heresies among you, that they which are approved may be made manifest among you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:20",
      "text": "When ye come together therefore into one place, this is not to eat the Lord’s supper.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:21",
      "text": "For in eating every one taketh before other his own supper: and one is hungry, and another is drunken.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:22",
      "text": "What? have ye not houses to eat and to drink in? or despise ye the church of God, and shame them that have not? What shall I say to you? shall I praise you in this? I praise you not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:23",
      "text": "For I have received of the Lord that which also I delivered unto you, That the Lord Jesus the same night in which he was betrayed took bread:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:24",
      "text": "And when he had given thanks, he brake it, and said, Take, eat: this is my body, which is broken for you: this do in remembrance of me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:25",
      "text": "After the same manner also he took the cup, when he had supped, saying, This cup is the new testament in my blood: this do ye, as oft as ye drink it, in remembrance of me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:26",
      "text": "For as often as ye eat this bread, and drink this cup, ye do shew the Lord’s death till he come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:27",
      "text": "Wherefore whosoever shall eat this bread, and drink this cup of the Lord, unworthily, shall be guilty of the body and blood of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:28",
      "text": "But let a man examine himself, and so let him eat of that bread, and drink of that cup.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:29",
      "text": "For he that eateth and drinketh unworthily, eateth and drinketh damnation to himself, not discerning the Lord’s body.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:30",
      "text": "For this cause many are weak and sickly among you, and many sleep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.31",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:31",
      "text": "For if we would judge ourselves, we should not be judged.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.32",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:32",
      "text": "But when we are judged, we are chastened of the Lord, that we should not be condemned with the world.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.33",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:33",
      "text": "Wherefore, my brethren, when ye come together to eat, tarry one for another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.11.34",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:34",
      "text": "And if any man hunger, let him eat at home; that ye come not together unto condemnation. And the rest will I set in order when I come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
